```text
packages/plugins/plugin-inbox/src/
  types/
    ExtractedFrom.ts            # ECHO relation (new)
    Mailbox.ts                  # add optional `extractors` config (edit)
  capabilities/
    MessageExtractor.ts         # capability + MatchResult/ExtractResult types (new)
  operations/
    extract-message.ts          # operation handler used by all three modes (new)
    google/gmail/sync.ts        # auto-on-arrival dispatch hook (edit)
  blueprints/
    inbox.ts                    # append ExtractMessage to toolDefinitions (edit)
  components/
    MessageActions.tsx          # menu surface; queries MessageExtractor registry (new)

packages/plugins/plugin-trip/src/
  extractors/
    TravelMessageExtractor.ts   # the MessageExtractor impl (new)
    parseUnitedFlight.ts        # pure parser for @united.com (new)
    parseBookingComHotel.ts     # pure parser for @booking.com (new)
    providers.ts                # known-domain → Provider lookup (new)
    __fixtures__/               # raw email bodies used in tests
  capabilities/
    index.ts                    # register TravelMessageExtractor (edit)
```

### Tests

```mdl
test parseUnitedFlight
  desc: Parser unit tests against fixture emails (canonical + edge cases).
  cases:
    - canonical eTicket itinerary → expected Booking + Flight Segment.
    - missing confirmation code → returns null.

test parseBookingComHotel
  desc: Parser unit tests against fixture emails.
  cases:
    - canonical hotel confirmation → expected Booking + Accommodation Segment.
    - missing check-in/check-out → returns null.

test TravelMessageExtractor
  desc: Dispatch, Trip resolution, and Account dedup.
  cases:
    - flight email + no existing Trip → creates new Trip wrapping flight dates.
    - flight email + one existing Trip → appends to most-recently-updated Trip.
    - flight email + target Trip ref → appends to target.
    - same provider + account number twice → reuses existing Account.

test extract-message operation
  desc: Operation handler integrates with the capability registry.
  cases:
    - manual mode: extractorId passed → calls exactly that extractor.
    - agent mode: no extractorId → picks highest-confidence match.
    - extractor throws → operation returns typed ExtractError; no partial writes.
```

```mdl
feat TripCalendarSource
  desc: >
    plugin-trip's CalendarEventSource impl. Projects Segments into
    CalendarEventLike values on demand; no materialised events are
    written. Tentative segments are included with a "tentative" hint
    (color / opacity left to the renderer).
  outputs (per Segment kind):
    - flight | train | boat | road: start = departAt, end = arriveAt
    - lodging: start = checkIn, end = checkOut
    - activity: start = departAt; end optional
  notes:
    - id format: `trip:<trip-id>:seg:<seg-id>` so projections are stable across query calls.
    - sourceObject is set to a Ref of the underlying Segment so consumers can navigate to it.
```

```mdl
feat TripMapMarkers
  desc: >
    plugin-trip contributes a MapCapabilities.MarkerProvider (from @dxos/plugin-map) that plots a
    Trip's segments: one marker per segment (keyed by segment id) plus origin→destination arcs for
    transport segments, with IATA-code geocoding for flights. Selection is single-mode against the
    trip's attendable context. plugin-map then renders the map (article toolbar toggle when the
    provider matches, and a map companion). The former in-plugin TripMapView / TripMapArticle and the
    `trip-map` surface are removed in favour of this generic integration.
  notes:
    - The TripArticle map toggle is shown only when a MarkerProvider matches the trip.
    - Selecting a marker dispatches LayoutOperation.Select so the segment stack stays in sync.
```

## Out of scope for Phase 1

- View definitions for Table / Map. The existing Table and Map view
  configurations are sufficient — Segments and Trips become queryable
  data sources for those views without new type contributions here.
- Markdown embedding surfaces. Trips and Segments use the generic
  article / embedded-surface mechanisms; no plugin-specific surface
  types are added.
- Currency conversion and price roll-ups. These are derived and live in
  view-side logic.
- `SegmentRequest` — multi-leg "desired travel" search input. Added when
  a real search provider is wired.
- `BookingFor` relation linking `Booking` → `Trip`. Added when a query
  needs Bookings without walking Segments.
- Splitting `BoatSegment` into ferry vs. cruise, and `RoadSegment` into
  per-mode variants. Revisit when usage demands richer per-mode typing.

## Out of scope for Phase 2

- Agent-backed extractor variants. The contract supports them (`extract`
  returns an `Effect`); a concrete impl is a follow-up.
- Additional carrier parsers (BA, Lufthansa, Eurostar, Avis, …). The v1
  parser registry is intentionally narrow (UA + Booking.com); new
  carriers are additive parser modules and unit tests.
- A UI for editing `Mailbox.extractors`. Developer-set in v1; UI lands
  when the auto-on-arrival mode gets validated in real mailboxes.
- A Trip picker in the manual extraction flow. v1 always resolves to
  most-recently-updated-or-new; a picker is a follow-up.
- `TripCalendarSource` (described above) — separate slice.

## Open follow-ups

- Confirm whether `Provider` should also replace `AccessToken.source`
  (currently `Hostname`); out of scope here but worth a follow-up to
  keep the model uniform.
- Smarter Trip resolution (date-range overlap, traveller match) for
  auto-on-arrival ingestion; v1 uses last-updated as a stand-in.
